-- NY AG says Citi unit to return $16 mln overcharged fees to consumers
-- By Narottam Medhora in Bangalore
-- Thu Oct 09, 2014 12:00AM EDT
-- None



Oct 9 (Reuters) - Citigroup Global Markets Inc (CGMI), a unit of Citigroup Inc <C.N>, has agreed to reimburse about $16 million to more than 31,000 customers, who were overcharged for advisory fees, the New York Attorney General said.

As per the agreement, some of the customers have already started to receive their refunds, Attorney General Eric Schneiderman said in a statement on Thursday.